        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer17026722" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer402785630605713505">I actually *read* this book, despite the fact that for some reason the above title is listed as an MP3 type thing.<br/>I&apos;m up and down with Jodi Picoult and this latest novel certainly reminded me why I sometimes can&apos;t stand her writing. It&apos;s very stereotypical (almost offensively so). Let&apos;s be serious Jodi, you are just not meant to write about life on &apos;death row&apos; in prison in a serious manner. The characters were very one sided and if she was trying to make a point about religion, the death penalty</span>
  <span id="freeText402785630605713505" style="display:none">I actually *read* this book, despite the fact that for some reason the above title is listed as an MP3 type thing.<br />I'm up and down with Jodi Picoult and this latest novel certainly reminded me why I sometimes can't stand her writing. It's very stereotypical (almost offensively so). Let's be serious Jodi, you are just not meant to write about life on 'death row' in prison in a serious manner. The characters were very one sided and if she was trying to make a point about religion, the death penalty, organ donation, the messiah, murder, (anything really), it fell very flat. I thought this book was very disappointing. Picoult is best when she takes on adolescent issues. She'sgood at writing from the point of view of a 16 year old.<br /></span>
