<div id="review_2304526413" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2304526413" />
    <a title="Darlene Stericker" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/62857526-darlene-stericker"><img alt="Darlene Stericker" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1574447277p2/62857526.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2304526413?book_show_action=true">Feb 22, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Darlene Stericker" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Darlene Stericker" href="/user/show/62857526-darlene-stericker">Darlene Stericker</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2304526413" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4663620685730878799">This book creeped me out. I am not sure what Picoult was thinking. She would lay out evidence and then later give contrary evidence. Then she would contradict herself once again. The twist was evident very early in the book. I feel very unsettled and not in a good way.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

